choices.text: undoubtedly the renewed effort to implant democracy in peace process. The UN governments had been pressurizing the government of Somaliland for the past 5 years and this had intensified a great deal in the past 18 months as the “Hariri reports” and the “Plea for Action on Somaliland” reports were circulated. The UN envoy to Somalia, Mr. Janani was quite vocal about the move and repeated this every single time when he found the ears receptive. This move towards democratization witnessed a bitter opposition from the feudal elite who are against any form of democratic rule, indicating their fear and reluctance to be in the receiving end of the popular wrath. Organized terrorist groups linked with the Islamic world, including some of the bigger mafia gangs of Somaliland, being aware of the will of the people to see a true system of democratic rule, almost went on a killing spree. Trial runs had been made to test the effect and viability of the threats and finally latched on the next available opportunity of a newly elected chairman of a local NGO to kill him. The Bondhere foundation chairman, Abdi Duhul was a grassroot rapscallion with big dreams. As the organiser and founder of the Bondhere Foundation he had gained wide area popularity and repute. Just after he had completed his graduation, Abdi had joined the World Bank and had exhibited resounding commitment and performance that advertised him straight into Shell Corporation where he served 4 years.
